# ── Supabase (recipe data + auth) ───────────────────────────────────────────
# Project URL and anon (public) key from Supabase → Project Settings → API.
# The anon key is publishable and safe in the client; Row-Level Security
# enforces per-user access. (Do NOT put the service_role key here.)
# Local dev: copy this file to `.env` and fill in, then run `npm run dev`.
# Production: set both in Netlify → Site settings → Environment variables.
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=
